tweet: Trustee Coley Canter asks the board to take this as an opportunity to agree to disagree and proposes the board take character training or resign members' ethics pledges.  Ford recommends St. John "take the high road" and issue an apology.

tweet: Some context: St. John has served on the board for 13 years. Ford was elected in Nov. 2010 and Kathy Florence Spradley was elected in May 2022.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Ford moves the conversation on to the next allegation (after determining that the board has proved what she did, but St. John alleges she didn't).   The next allegation is that she (falsely) accused the district's counsel (lawyer) of sleeping during the last meeting.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: St. John asks another board member to weigh in, and is interrupted and is told that is inappropriate.  A community member erupts and says that Ford is not calling decorum on the board members' back-and-forth.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Ford asks members of the public not to laugh (or make noise or clap, etc.) or they will be removed.   St. John now asks not to be interrupted. She said that emails accusing her of the actions Ford outlines is false.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: When he has completed his statement, St. John calls his statement "a pretty prepared statement" and asks if he had intended to read it aloud to the public anyways.  Ford asks St. John not to "speculate" on his statement, which is met by laughs from the crowd.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Ford says that during GCISD's Board of Trustees last meeting, St. John was witnessed calling another board member a "b----" and a "f-- b---".

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Ford is interrupted by a meeting attendee who says she can't hear, but he asks her multiple times to be quiet and says he doesn't control the sound.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Ford adds that he hoped to have the discussion privately so that St. John's "behavior might change."  He continues by reading the board's ethics pledge.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: St. John said she asked Board of Trustees President Casey Ford why she was on the agenda and said he would not tell her why.  Ford says he wanted the discussion to be private because he doesn't believe in "airing the board's dirty laundry publicly."

tweet: A post-script thanks to the Edison and Ford Winter Estates for this history of the Sialia:    https://t.co/Lh9kl1u5As

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: Side note:  There are newspaper reports of Ford‚Äôs son, Edsel, crashing a yacht called the ‚ÄúSialia‚Äù in 1929. But this may have been a different vessel.  The official ownership log of the original Sialia makes no mention of Edsel Ford. A little unclear‚Ä¶   https://t.co/4qN7DVLvnc

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: Ford later tried to retool the Sialia to improve its speed.   But his ‚Äúupgrades‚Äù apparently had the opposite effect. The ship went slower.  And shortly afterward, the automobile titan sold his ‚ÄúBluebird of happiness.‚Äù

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: Henry Ford, Thomas Edison, Harvey Firestone, and the famous naturalist John Burroughs called themselves the ‚ÄúFour Vagabonds.‚Äù And they took a series of summer trips together.  The 1924 trip on the Sialia was to Michigan‚Äôs Upper Peninsula.  https://t.co/yQyTLWINJ4

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: Ford owned the Sialia from 1920 to 1927. Every time he boarded, the ship raised a flag that said ‚ÄúBluebird of Happiness.‚Äù The Sialia crisscrossed the upper midwest during this era.  And in 1924 it was involved in one of Ford‚Äôs famous ‚ÄúVagabonds‚Äù trips.

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: So Henry Ford bought the yacht. But nearly as soon as Ford bought it, the yacht was commandeered by the U.S. Navy for use in World War I. It remained in Uncle Sam‚Äôs service for three years.  The ship survived the war‚Ä¶and Ford re-purchased it in 1920.

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: In 1917, Henry Ford himself took an interest in the yacht. Ford‚Äôs interest may have been related to the name.   Sialia is the genus name for bluebirds.  And Ford apparently had a formative childhood memory about seeing a bluebird nest with his father:  https://t.co/Lh9kl1txKU

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: The Sialia was built for a Chicago inventor and industrialist named J.K. Stewart ‚Äî who was probably most famous for mass-producing speedometers.   Stewart‚Äôs speedometers were used in the Ford Model T.  More on Stewart's unusual life here:  https://t.co/v8N6EgViCj  https://t.co/n0pRLZovFV
